const duplicatedCore = [...coreLanguages, ...coreLanguages, ...coreLanguages, ...coreLanguages];
const duplicatedInfra = [...infrastructure, ...infrastructure, ...infrastructure, ...infrastructure];
const duplicatedExtra = [...additionalTech, ...additionalTech, ...additionalTech, ...additionalTech];
---

<section class="py-20 animate-fade-in-up">
    <h2 class="mb-12 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-zinc-100 sm:text-4xl transition-colors duration-300">
        About Me & Technical Trajectory
    </h2>
    
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-zinc-400 lg:col-span-2 transition-colors duration-300">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-zinc-200 transition-colors duration-300">Background & Evolution</h3>
            <p>
                Hello, I am Iago Fernandez Perlo. My trajectory in engineering began in childhood, driven by a natural curiosity for logic, mathematics, and physical creation. I spent my early years tinkering with Arduino boards, building simple machines, and exploring block-based programming. This hands-on hardware experience quickly evolved into developing video game modifications, building early websites, and writing automated scripts for Linux environments.
            </p>
            <p>
                A rigorous foundation in analytical thinking was established through competitive problem solving. A broad passion for scientific inquiry led me to qualify for the national Mathematics, Physics, and Chemistry Olympiads, alongside <em>LigaMAT</em> (a competitive national mathematical league) and regional robotics competitions. This continuous search for optimal models culminated in graduating with the <em>Premio Extraordinario de Bachillerato</em> (Extraordinary High School Award) and achieving <em>Matrícula de Honor</em> (Highest Honors). Driven by these achievements, I enrolled in the Dual BSc in Mathematics and Computer Engineering.
            </p>
            <p>
                As my technical scope broadened during my university studies, I developed a strong focus on cybersecurity. Utilizing distributions like Kali Linux and Parrot OS, I gained practical experience by participating in Capture The Flag (CTF) events and developing custom cryptographic utilities and reverse shells. To solidify these operational skills, I completed specialized coursework accredited by INCIBE (Spanish National Cybersecurity Institute). Furthermore, my ongoing Erasmus+ exchange at the University of Lodz has proven my capacity for rapid adaptation and effective communication within novel, dynamic international environments.
            </p>
            <p>
                Today, my core focus remains squarely on the intersection of low-level optimization and advanced mathematical algorithms. This is currently reflected in my work as a Software Engineering Intern at RAPOSa (CITMAGA). In this role, I leverage a strong mathematical background in optimization to integrate low-level solver APIs into the core software architecture. By engineering solutions in C++, I bridge the gap between theoretical mathematics and high-performance software execution, demanding strict minimization of temporal and spatial complexity.
            </p>
            <p>
                Looking ahead, I am focused on completing my dual degree and transitioning into a professional role that leverages this unique intersection of disciplines. I am actively exploring opportunities in high-performance computing, low-level systems engineering, and the development of mission-critical software. I am also considering specialized Master's programs to further deepen my technical expertise in advanced computational models and algorithmic optimization.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-zinc-200 transition-colors duration-300">Academic Foundation</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
